      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "No point to using <code>LocalDateTime</code> as that class purposely has no concept of time zone nor offset-from-UTC. Use that only when zone/offset is unknown or not relevant. Instead use <code>LocalDate</code> and pass a <code>ZoneId</code> when calling its <code>now</code> method. See the <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/37658868/642706\">correct Answer</a> by Jacob van Lingen."
