      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I suggest always passing the optional time zone (or offset-from-UTC) to that <code>now</code> method. If omitted, the JVM‘s current default time zone is implicitly and silently applied. That default lies outside your control and can change at any moment, even <i>during</i> runtime. Example: <code>LocalDate.now( ZoneId.of( &quot;America&#47;Montreal&quot; )</code>."
