    "answer_id" : 46516438,
    "question_id" : 11882926,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have created a function to make the task easier.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>For 7 days after dateString: <code>dateCalculate(dateString,\"yyyy-MM-dd\",7);</code></p></li>\n<li><p>To get 7 days upto dateString: <code>dateCalculate(dateString,\"yyyy-MM-dd\",-7);</code></p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n\n<pre><code>public static String dateCalculate(String dateString, String dateFormat, int days) {\n    Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();\n    SimpleDateFormat s = new SimpleDateFormat(dateFormat);\n    try {\n        cal.setTime(s.parse(dateString));\n    } catch (ParseException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n    cal.add(Calendar.DATE, days);\n    return s.format(cal.getTime());\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
